                    </div>
                    <span>It is an old book so some of the info is rather dated.<p>However, it is good for a historical perspective and it gives an ok overview of the whole concept.<p>It will not give you answers to what you need to do as much of the spamming techniques have changed since it's publishing.<p>For example HTML based spam, spam fighing software, and Baysean formula came after this.<p>It was a book for its time but it has passed.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">No userful information</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>1</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
